 <!-- Introduction -->
 <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
 <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">Sourcing from China can be highly profitable. But it also carries real risks. Fake factories, counterfeit certifications, and outright scams can wipe out your investment overnight. For any importer new to the Chinese supply chain, the stakes are high.</p>
 
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">About 30% of first-time China importers run into supplier issues in their first year. Most of these problems are preventable. You just need a clear factory verification process. This works the same whether you are sourcing <a href="/products/wireless-charger" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">wireless chargers</a>, <a href="/products/power-bank" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">power chargers</a>, or any other electronics.</p>

 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">This checklist covers every step of verifying a Chinese manufacturer. It walks you through basic documents, factory audits, QC systems, and compliance standards. Use it as your roadmap, rom basic documentation to factory audits, quality control systems, and social compliance standards. It will help you build a strong, long-term partnership with a factory you can trust, one that protects both your brand and your bottom line.</p>

 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">According to a 2024 Alibaba supplier quality report, only 12% of electronics suppliers on B2B platforms pass comprehensive third-party factory audits, making independent verification critical before committing any order.</p>

 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">According to the China General Administration of Customs, Shenzhen port exported over $12 billion in phone and charger accessories in 2024, highlighting the massive scale of China's electronics manufacturing ecosystem.</p>

 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">We have laid out each phase in order. You can work through it step by step, whether you are checking suppliers from afar or visiting the factory in person for an <a href="/service" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">OEM/ODM audit</a>. Every section gives you clear actions you can take right away, no matter your experience level.</p>
 </div>

