 <!-- 3. Document Verification Checklist -->
 <section id="document-verification" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">3. Document Verification Checklist</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Before engaging deeply with any supplier, you must verify their legal existence and business credentials. This foundational step prevents most common scams and ensures you're dealing with a legitimate business entity that can be held accountable.</p>
 
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Business License</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Request a copy of their unified social credit code certificate. Verify it through the <a href="https://www.gsxt.gov.cn/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">National Enterprise Credit Information Publicity System</a>. Check three things. First, does the registered capital match their claimed capability? Second, does the business scope include manufacturing? Third, does the establishment date align with their claimed experience?</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs"><strong>Red flag:</strong> Business license shows different company name than communications, or registration is less than 2 years old with no verifiable track record.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Import/Export License</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Verify they possess legitimate import/export capabilities through the <a href="http://www.customs.gov.cn/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">Chinese Customs Administration</a>. This confirms they're either a trading company or manufacturer actively engaged in international trade. Request their customs registration number.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Trading companies without manufacturing capability may resell products from other factories, making quality control and pricing transparency difficult.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Tax Registration Certificate</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Verify they have proper tax registration for export transactions. This includes general taxpayer status for VAT invoice capability. Request sample invoices to verify authenticity.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Production Permit (if applicable)</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">For regulated products like electronics, verify they have required production permits and industry certifications. Check with the relevant regulatory body.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Factory Photos & Video Verification</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Request full factory documentation. Ask for exterior shots with the building address, interior photos of production lines (timestamped), office areas, warehouse space, and staff common areas. Cross-reference the location with satellite imagery on <a href="https://www.google.com/maps" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">Google Maps</a> or <a href="https://world.taobao.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">Baidu Maps</a>.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs"><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Ask for a live video call or request specific photos (holding today's newspaper, specific handwritten sign) to confirm they're actually at the claimed location.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Contact Information Verification</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Verify phone numbers through WeChat or WhatsApp verification. Confirm they use a company email domain (not @gmail.com, @yahoo.com, or free email services). Be suspicious of only having WeChat contact without verified business credentials.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 </div>
 </section>

