 <!-- 4. How to Verify Certification Authenticity? -->
 <section id="certification-authenticity" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">4. How to Verify Certification Authenticity?</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Counterfeit certifications are rampant in Chinese manufacturing. Fake certifications are a real problem. A factory may show impressive certificates on their website. But many are forged, expired, or simply do not apply to the products you need. Always verify every certification yourself. There is no substitute for independent checks when protecting your business.</p>

 <div class="mb-6">
 <img src="/image/blog/oem-vs-odm-guide/oem-odm-wireless-charging-qc-testing.webp"
 alt="Factory QC testing for wireless charger certification - verifying compliance and authenticity"
 title="QC Testing - Certification Verification"
 width="800" height="600" loading="lazy" decoding="async"
 class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
 <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm mt-3">Verify certifications through official databases, not just factory-provided documents</p>
 </div>

 <div class="space-y-4">
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">ISO 9001 Quality Management</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Verify ISO 9001 through the <a href="https://www.iso.org/validate-certificate" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">ISO Certificate Validation Portal</a> or the certifying body's website. Check three things. Does the certificate scope match your product category? Is the validity period still active? Is the certification body accredited (CNAS for China)?</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs"><strong>Watch out:</strong> Some factories display ISO 9001 but the scope only covers certain processes, not their actual manufacturing operations.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Product-Specific Certifications</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">For electronics, verify each certification with its issuing body. Use the <a href="https://www.wirelesspowerconsortium.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">Qi Certified Product Database</a> for wireless chargers. Check <a href="https://www.ce-marking.org/ce-marking.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">CE marking requirements</a> for European compliance. For US market access, use the <a href="https://www.fcc.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">FCC SDoC database</a>.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs"><strong>Critical:</strong> Request the actual test reports, not just certificates. Reports show exactly what was tested and the methodology used.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">RoHS & REACH Compliance</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Request test reports for hazardous substance restrictions. RoHS compliance is mandatory for electronics sold in EU markets. Verify with the <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/environment/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">European Commission environment website</a>.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Quality Manual & Procedures</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Request quality management documentation. ISO 9001 certified factories maintain detailed process records including work instructions, inspection procedures, and non-conformance handling processes. Review these during your <a href="/about" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">factory evaluation</a> if possible.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 </div>

 <div class="bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-brandBlue p-6 mt-8">
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-3">Official Verification Resources</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">Use these authoritative databases to verify certifications independently:</p>
 <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
 <li>, a href="https://www.iso.org/validate-certificate" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">ISO Certificate Verification</a> - Verify quality management certifications</li>
 <li>, a href="https://www.wirelesspowerconsortium.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">Qi Certified Product Database</a> - Verify wireless charging compatibility</li>
 <li>, a href="https://www.ce-marking.org/ce-marking.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">CE Marking Guide</a> - Understand European compliance requirements</li>
 <li>, a href="https://www.fcc.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">FCC SDoC Database</a> - Verify US radio frequency compliance</li>
 <li>, a href="https://www.cnas.org.cn/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">CNAS Database</a> - Verify Chinese accreditation bodies</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- 5. Production Facility Inspection Points -->
 <section id="production-facility" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">5. Production Facility Inspection Points</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Understanding a factory's actual production capability is essential for forecasting, quality assurance, and avoiding delays. Use this checklist during a video tour or in-person audit to assess whether the factory can handle your volume requirements consistently.</p>
 <!-- Factory SMT Line Image -->
 <div class="mb-8">
 <img src="/image/factory/factory-smt-line.webp"
 alt="Factory SMT production line for charger PCB assembly - automated manufacturing equipment verification"
 title="Factory SMT Line - Production Capability Verification"
 width="2000" height="1335" loading="lazy" decoding="async"
 class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
 <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm mt-3">Automated SMT production lines indicate professional manufacturing capability</p>
 </div>
 
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Production Capacity Verification</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Verify monthly output capability. Professional electronics factories can produce 100,000 to 1,000,000+ units monthly depending on product complexity. Ask for production records from the past 6 months showing actual output, not just claimed capacity. Cross-reference with their raw material procurement records.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs"><strong>Red flag:</strong> Claimed capacity significantly exceeds what their equipment or workforce can realistically support.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Manufacturing Equipment Assessment</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Request photos or video of production equipment. For electronics, look for SMT lines (surface mount technology), AOI (automated optical inspection) machines, soldering equipment, testing stations, and packaging lines. Count the equipment and assess modernization. Newer equipment typically indicates better capability and consistency.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs"><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Ask about equipment maintenance schedules and last upgrade dates.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Minimum Order Quantity (MOQ) Reality Check</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Understand their MOQ structure. Typical OEM orders range from 500-5,000 units depending on product complexity. A MOQ that's too low (under 100 units) may indicate they purchase from other factories. A MOQ that's too high may strain your cash flow. Evaluate whether their <a href="/service" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">MOQ aligns with your business model</a>.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Lead Time Reliability</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Standard production lead time is 20-30 days after sample approval for existing products. New mold tooling typically requires 45-60 days. Ask for their on-time delivery rate over the past year. A reliable factory maintains 95%+ on-time delivery and can provide references from other buyers.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Workforce Evaluation</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Assess the workforce size and organization. Professional factories employ dedicated QC staff (typically 5-15% of workforce), engineering teams, and clear organizational structure. Ask about employee turnover rate,, high turnover suggests poor management and potential quality issues.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Raw Material Sourcing</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Understand their component sourcing strategy. Professional factories maintain relationships with certified component suppliers. Request information on key component sources, especially for safety-critical parts. Be cautious if they can't identify their major chip suppliers or battery sources.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- 6. Quality Control Verification -->
 <section id="quality-control-verification" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">6. Quality Control Verification</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Quality control separates professional factories from commodity suppliers. A robust QC system isn't just about catching defective products,, it's about preventing defects from occurring in the first place through systematic process control.</p>
 <div class="mb-6">
 <img src="/image/blog/how-to-choose-factory/wireless-charger-factory-audit-retail-packaging.webp"
 alt="Factory quality control inspection - packaging and finished product verification for charger OEM production"
 title="QC Inspection - Factory Audit"
 width="800" height="600" loading="lazy" decoding="async"
 class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
 <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm mt-3">Professional QC inspection ensures consistent product quality across every production batch</p>
 </div>

 <div class="space-y-4">
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">QC Process Documentation</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Request a flow chart of their complete QC process. Professional factories implement multi-stage inspection including IQC (incoming quality control), IPQC (in-process quality control), FQC (final quality control), and OQC (outgoing quality control). Each stage should have documented procedures, acceptance criteria, and recording systems.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs"><strong>Ask for:</strong> Their QC flowchart, inspection standards document, and sample inspection reports.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Testing Equipment Calibration</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Professional factories invest in comprehensive testing capabilities. For electronics, this includes integrated testing systems, aging test equipment, Hi-Pot testers, function testers, and safety testing equipment. Verify these exist and ask about calibration schedules,, equipment should be calibrated annually by certified labs.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Defect Rate Standards</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Ask about their target defect rate. Professional factories aim for under 1% defective rate. Excellent factories target under 0.3%. Request data showing actual defect rates from recent orders. Be suspicious if they claim "zero defects",, this is unrealistic and may indicate they haven't measured accurately.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Aging Test Policy</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">For power products like chargers, aging tests are critical. Wireless chargers should undergo 2-4 hour full-power aging tests. 100% testing is best practice for safety-critical parameters. Verify their testing protocol covers thermal performance, charging efficiency, and safety cutoffs.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">First Article Inspection (FAI)</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Verify they conduct FAI for new orders. This involves detailed inspection of the first 10-50 units from a production run to validate the process before full production begins. This catches tooling or process issues early, preventing large-scale quality problems.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- 7. Financial Stability Assessment -->
 <section id="financial-stability" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">7. Financial Stability Assessment</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">A factory's financial health directly impacts their ability to fulfill long-term orders, invest in quality equipment, and maintain consistent production. Assessing financial stability helps you avoid partners who may go bankrupt mid-order or cut corners to stay afloat.</p>
 
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Business History & Track Record</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Verify how long they've been in business. Factories established before 2010 with continuous operation demonstrate stability. Request client references and actually contact them. Ask about payment terms they've offered and whether they honor them consistently.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Payment Term Negotiation</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Standard terms for new relationships are 30% deposit, 70% balance before shipment. Be cautious of factories insisting on 100% advance payment,, this removes your use. Similarly, be wary of factories accepting very long payment terms without credit checks, as this may indicate desperation for business.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs"><strong>Learn more about our payment terms and <a href="/contact" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">negotiation process</a>.</strong></p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Credit Check & Background Research</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Conduct basic due diligence using resources like <a href="https://www.tianyancha.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">Tianyancha</a> or <a href="https://www.qichacha.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">Qichacha</a> to verify registration information, litigation history, and business connections. These platforms show if the company has outstanding legal judgments or operational anomalies.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- 8. Social Compliance Audit -->
 <section id="social-compliance" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">8. Social Compliance Audit</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Social compliance is increasingly critical for Western markets. Brands face reputational risk and potential legal liability for supply chain labor practices. A comprehensive social compliance audit protects your brand and ensures ethical production standards.</p>
 
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Labor Practice Verification</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Request information about working hours, wages, and benefits. Verify compliance with local labor laws including maximum working hours, overtime regulations, and minimum wage requirements. Professional factories maintain employee records and pay social insurance as required by Chinese law.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">SA8000 Certification (if applicable)</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">SA8000 is the leading social certification program for factories. While not mandatory, factories with <a href="https://www.sa-intl.org/sa8000/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">SA8000 certification</a> demonstrate commitment to ethical labor practices. Verify through the SAAS directory if claimed.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Environmental Compliance</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Verify environmental permits and waste management practices. Manufacturing facilities require environmental assessment approvals. Request their environmental impact assessment or pollution discharge permits for relevant authorities.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Health & Safety Standards</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Assess workplace safety conditions including fire exits, emergency procedures, and hazardous material handling. Request their safety inspection records and worker compensation insurance documentation.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Communication Test -->
 <section id="communication-assessment" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">9. Communication & Professional Assessment</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Communication quality often predicts relationship success. Professional factories maintain clear, responsive communication as a standard practice. Use these checkpoints to evaluate their communication and professionalism.</p>
 
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Response Time Analysis</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Test their response time over several days. Professional suppliers respond within 24 hours during business days. Note response quality,, not just speed. Do they answer your questions thoroughly, or give vague responses? Slow or evasive communication often indicates problems that will intensify after you place orders.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">English Proficiency Assessment</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Assess English communication skills, especially for technical discussions. While not every staff member needs fluent English, key contacts (sales manager, QC manager, project manager) should communicate effectively. Misunderstandings due to language barriers cause costly production errors.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Technical Knowledge Evaluation</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Ask specific technical questions about your product. Professional factories have knowledgeable staff who can discuss materials, processes, and specifications confidently. Vague answers or "we can do anything" claims without specifics are red flags.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Sample Evaluation -->
 <section id="sample-evaluation" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">10. How to Evaluate Samples from a Factory?</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Samples are your best preview of production quality. Never skip sample evaluation, regardless of how impressive a factory's credentials appear. This phase reveals the truth about their actual manufacturing capability.</p>
 <!-- Sample Product Image -->
 <div class="mb-8">
 <img src="/image/product/power-bank/wop69-2in1-charger.webp"
 alt="OEM/ODM charger sample evaluation - 2-in-1 power bank and GaN charger for quality testing"
 title="Charger Sample Evaluation - OEM Quality Testing"
 width="1200" height="1200" loading="lazy" decoding="async"
 class="w-full max-w-lg mx-auto rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
 <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm mt-3">Request samples to verify build quality, charging speed, and certification compliance</p>
 </div>
 
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Sample Availability & Lead Time</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Professional factories offer samples from existing products. Typical lead time is 3-7 days for stock items. Custom samples require 7-14 days. Be cautious of factories claiming they can ship samples "tomorrow",, this suggests they're dropshipping, not manufacturing.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Sample Cost & Refund Policy</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Clarify sample costs upfront. Many professional factories refund sample costs on bulk orders (typically 3-5x sample cost credited to first order). Be wary of extremely cheap samples,, this may indicate low quality or misrepresentation.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Comprehensive Quality Testing</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2">Test samples thoroughly using your own criteria. For chargers, test charging speed, thermal performance under load, build quality, safety features, cable durability, and packaging. Compare against your specifications and competitor products. <a href="/about" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">Our factory provides detailed testing reports</a> with every sample.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 
 <label class="flex items-start gap-4 p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
 <input type="checkbox" class="w-6 h-6 mt-1 accent-brandOrange">
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Pre-Production Sample Approval</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Before bulk production, require pre-production samples. These confirm materials, colors, and workmanship match your specifications. Document approval signatures and keep records. Never begin production without written approval of pre-production samples.</p>
 </div>
 </label>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Warning Signs Section -->
 <section id="red-flags" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-4">11. Red Flags: Warning Signs to Watch</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Recognizing warning signs early saves you from costly mistakes. If you encounter multiple red flags, reconsider the supplier regardless of how attractive their pricing or credentials appear.</p>
 
 <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
 <svg class="icon-xmark text-red-500 mt-1" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 384 512">
 <path d="M55.1 73.4c-12.5-12.5-32.8-12.5-45.3 0s-12.5 32.8 0 45.3L147.2 256 9.9 393.4c-12.5 12.5-12.5 32.8 0 45.3s32.8 12.5 45.3 0L192.5 301.3 329.9 438.6c12.5 12.5 32.8 12.5 45.3 0s12.5-32.8 0-45.3L237.8 256 375.1 118.6c12.5-12.5 12.5-32.8 0-45.3s-32.8-12.5-45.3 0L192.5 210.7 55.1 73.4z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Refuses to provide any documentation</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Legitimate factories are registered and can provide business licenses, certifications, and references. Refusal to share basic documentation is a major warning sign.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
 <svg class="icon-xmark text-red-500 mt-1" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 384 512">
 <path d="M55.1 73.4c-12.5-12.5-32.8-12.5-45.3 0s-12.5 32.8 0 45.3L147.2 256 9.9 393.4c-12.5 12.5-12.5 32.8 0 45.3s32.8 12.5 45.3 0L192.5 301.3 329.9 438.6c12.5 12.5 32.8 12.5 45.3 0s12.5-32.8 0-45.3L237.8 256 375.1 118.6c12.5-12.5 12.5-32.8 0-45.3s-32.8-12.5-45.3 0L192.5 210.7 55.1 73.4z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Prices too good to be true</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">If pricing is 30%+ below market rates, something is wrong,, usually quality, authenticity, or there's no actual goods to deliver. Get multiple quotes and understand market pricing.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
 <svg class="icon-xmark text-red-500 mt-1" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 384 512">
 <path d="M55.1 73.4c-12.5-12.5-32.8-12.5-45.3 0s-12.5 32.8 0 45.3L147.2 256 9.9 393.4c-12.5 12.5-12.5 32.8 0 45.3s32.8 12.5 45.3 0L192.5 301.3 329.9 438.6c12.5 12.5 32.8 12.5 45.3 0s12.5-32.8 0-45.3L237.8 256 375.1 118.6c12.5-12.5 12.5-32.8 0-45.3s-32.8-12.5-45.3 0L192.5 210.7 55.1 73.4z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">No sample policy or refuses samples</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Professional manufacturers stand behind their products with samples. Refusal to provide samples indicates they either can't manufacture to your specs or have something to hide.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
 <svg class="icon-xmark text-red-500 mt-1" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 384 512">
 <path d="M55.1 73.4c-12.5-12.5-32.8-12.5-45.3 0s-12.5 32.8 0 45.3L147.2 256 9.9 393.4c-12.5 12.5-12.5 32.8 0 45.3s32.8 12.5 45.3 0L192.5 301.3 329.9 438.6c12.5 12.5 32.8 12.5 45.3 0s12.5-32.8 0-45.3L237.8 256 375.1 118.6c12.5-12.5 12.5-32.8 0-45.3s-32.8-12.5-45.3 0L192.5 210.7 55.1 73.4z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Poor communication or delayed responses</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Communication problems during the sales phase multiply after payment. If they can't respond promptly now, expect worse after you've committed money.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
 <svg class="icon-xmark text-red-500 mt-1" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 384 512">
 <path d="M55.1 73.4c-12.5-12.5-32.8-12.5-45.3 0s-12.5 32.8 0 45.3L147.2 256 9.9 393.4c-12.5 12.5-12.5 32.8 0 45.3s32.8 12.5 45.3 0L192.5 301.3 329.9 438.6c12.5 12.5 32.8 12.5 45.3 0s12.5-32.8 0-45.3L237.8 256 375.1 118.6c12.5-12.5 12.5-32.8 0-45.3s-32.8-12.5-45.3 0L192.5 210.7 55.1 73.4z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Can't verify certifications independently</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">If a factory claims certifications but you can't verify them through official channels, assume they're fake. Always verify independently.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
 <svg class="icon-xmark text-red-500 mt-1" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 384 512">
 <path d="M55.1 73.4c-12.5-12.5-32.8-12.5-45.3 0s-12.5 32.8 0 45.3L147.2 256 9.9 393.4c-12.5 12.5-12.5 32.8 0 45.3s32.8 12.5 45.3 0L192.5 301.3 329.9 438.6c12.5 12.5 32.8 12.5 45.3 0s12.5-32.8 0-45.3L237.8 256 375.1 118.6c12.5-12.5 12.5-32.8 0-45.3s-32.8-12.5-45.3 0L192.5 210.7 55.1 73.4z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Only accepts Western Union or informal payments</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Professional factories accept bank transfers, letter of credit, and payment terms through established financial channels. Western Union is for personal transactions, not B2B manufacturing.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
 <svg class="icon-xmark text-red-500 mt-1" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 384 512">
 <path d="M55.1 73.4c-12.5-12.5-32.8-12.5-45.3 0s-12.5 32.8 0 45.3L147.2 256 9.9 393.4c-12.5 12.5-12.5 32.8 0 45.3s32.8 12.5 45.3 0L192.5 301.3 329.9 438.6c12.5 12.5 32.8 12.5 45.3 0s12.5-32.8 0-45.3L237.8 256 375.1 118.6c12.5-12.5 12.5-32.8 0-45.3s-32.8-12.5-45.3 0L192.5 210.7 55.1 73.4z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Asks for full payment upfront with no protection</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Reputable factories offer payment terms that protect both parties. 100% advance payment removes all your use and risk protection.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
 <svg class="icon-xmark text-red-500 mt-1" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 384 512">
 <path d="M55.1 73.4c-12.5-12.5-32.8-12.5-45.3 0s-12.5 32.8 0 45.3L147.2 256 9.9 393.4c-12.5 12.5-12.5 32.8 0 45.3s32.8 12.5 45.3 0L192.5 301.3 329.9 438.6c12.5 12.5 32.8 12.5 45.3 0s12.5-32.8 0-45.3L237.8 256 375.1 118.6c12.5-12.5 12.5-32.8 0-45.3s-32.8-12.5-45.3 0L192.5 210.7 55.1 73.4z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Pressure tactics and limited-time offers</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Legitimate suppliers don't pressure you into quick decisions. "Order now or lose the price" tactics indicate desperation or fraud, not professional business relationships.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

